FA_CP

Copyright 2026 Benqi Liu.

This repository contains the FA_CP implementation used for the quadratic
programming experiments in the paper "Restarted Reflected Halpern
Acceleration for Augmented Primal--Dual Methods".

The main additions in this distribution include the FA_CP augmented
fixed-point/correction update, guarded sigma policy, Maros--Meszaros Table 1
benchmark scripts, and release renaming/documentation. Benchmark formulations
that use lifted or eliminated variables are expected to be supplied through the
input data/preprocessing pipeline used to create the QPS/MPS files.

Some low-level GPU solver infrastructure and QP input/benchmarking utilities
are adapted from Apache-2.0 licensed first-order optimization software. The
FA_CP augmented fixed-point/correction update, guarded sigma policy, benchmark
policies, release scripts, and documentation in this distribution are provided
as Benqi Liu's research implementation. Original third-party copyright and
license notices are retained in the corresponding source files.

Related restarted primal-dual QP papers and public software are cited only for
benchmark context and comparative baselines. This repository is an independent
research implementation and is not affiliated with, sponsored by, or endorsed
by any third-party authors or their institutions.
